Package com.apple.audio.toolbox

Interface Summary
AudioConverterDataSupplier This is a callback that is used by AudioConverter.fillBuffer to get input data to convert.
AUGraphRenderNotification This is a callback that an app can register with an AUGraph to gain notifications before and after a renderSlice is called on an the graph.
AUParameterListener Classes implement this interface to receive notifications of changes in parameters of an AudioUnit
 

Class Summary
ATConstants  
AUConnectionInfo This class contains information about a connection that exists in an AUGraph.
AudioConverter This class represents an AudioConverter that converts formats of audio data.
AudioConverterInputData This structure is passed back from the request for more data made by the AudioConverter.fillBuffer call to its AudioConverterDataSupplier interface.
AUGraph The AUGraph APIs are responsible for representing the description of a set of AudioUnit components, as well as the audio connections between their inputs and outputs.
AUListener This is used to both register notifications of changes to AudioUnit parameter values and to change those values so other listeners can receive notifictions of those changes.
AUMIDIController  
AUNode This class represents a node identifier when added to a AUGraph
AUParameter  
ExtendedControlEvent  
ExtendedNoteOnEvent  
ExtendedTempoEvent Used to retrieve tempo events (beats per minute) from a MusicTrack
MusicEventIterator Some Notes on using the iterator to move through events in the track.
MusicPlayer A MusicPlayer plays a MusicSequence.
MusicSequence A MusicSequence contains an arbitrary number of tracks (MusicTrack) each of which contains time-stamped (typically in units of beats, or seconds ) events in time-increasing order.
MusicTrack A Music track is attached from an MusicSequence and contains events that are ordered by their time values.
